FIG. 9(a) is a map showing the relationship between the threshold value of the lateral acceleration and the fork height according to the third embodiment that is used when the load weight is less than a threshold value;


FIG. 9(b) is a map like FIG. 9(a) that is used when the load weight is equal to or greater than a threshold value; and


FIG. 10 is a map showing the relationship among the fork height, the load weight and the threshold value of the lateral acceleration according to a fourth embodiment.
